LONDON - Britain's Prince Harry is engaged to his US actress girlfriend Meghan Markle with the marriage due to take place in the spring of 2018, his father Prince Charles announced in a statement on Monday. Harry (33) currently fifth-in-line to the British throne, and Markle (36), best known for her role in the US TV legal drama "Suits", became engaged earlier this month, the statement issued by Clarence House said. "Prince Harry has informed Her Majesty The Queen and other close members of his family. Prince Harry has also sought and received the blessing of Ms Markle's parents," the statement said. Reuters